f=Cybersecurity/warden/custom/third-party-risk/assets/vendor-assessment-template.md · h1:Vendor Security Assessment [vendor] [date]=Assess proportionate data access. Feeds warden's risk-register. Critical touches crown-jewel data (veil classification). · h2:Scope=Data touched: [class veil none internal confidential PII regulated], Access: [systems/scope] Business function: [what use them for], Critical vendor: [y/n] Concentration/single-point-of-failure: [y/n] · h2:Posture=Certifications: [SOC (scope/exceptions) ISO 27001 none questionnaire], Security questionnaire: [key answers gaps], Breach history: [known incidents], Sub-processors: [who else touches our data downstream] · h2:Contract (the controls)=Data-processing agreement (DPA) place, Breach-notification clause (they notify within ___, Security requirements specified, Right-to-audit evidence, Data return/deletion exit · h2:Outcome=Risk score register [R-ref] Treatment: [adopt adopt-with-controls reject], Re-assessment cadence: [config], vendor breach cortex veil breach-notification review